            <h3 class="modern-card-title">Defense</h3>
            <p class="modern-card-description"> The ₹3500 Crore estimate for the defense sector reflects Vardhman’s focused niche in E&M infrastructure for Army Aviation and defense establishments. While India’s overall defense budget is projected to reach ₹6.8 lakh crore in 2025–26, Vardhman’s target represents a realistic share of this vast market. With India’s defense market estimated at USD 17.3 billion (~₹1.43 lakh crore) in 2024 (IMARC, May 2025), the figure aligns with its specialized and addressable segment.</p>
            <a href="/defense" class="modern-card-button">View Details</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modern-card">
          <div class="modern-card-img" style="background-image: url('/images/4.png');"></div>
          <div class="modern-card-content">
            <h3 class="modern-card-title">Railways</h3>
            <p class="modern-card-description"> The ₹2500 Crore estimate for the MES/Railways sector aligns closely with India’s current smart meter market size. IMARC reported the market at USD 288.3 million (₹2393 Crores) in 2024, while Zion estimated it at USD 212 million (₹1759 Crores) in 2023, with projections reaching over ₹23,000 Crores by 2032 at a 33.3% CAGR. With Vardhman actively entering this space and securing MES smart metering projects, the ₹2500 Crore figure reflects a credible and focused market opportunity.
</p>
            <a href="/railways" class="modern-card-button">View Details</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

